{
  "doc_id": "8543",
  "text": "PSO is an evolutionary algorithm used for the optimisation of continuous and multidimensional search spaces [CITATION_1] . PSO has been used in [CITATION_2] for optimisation of fuzzy logic controllers to improve the battery lifetime in Industrial Wireless Sensor Networks. In [CITATION_3] , the authors have used PSO and fuzzy clustering to determine the cluster heads. The initial clustering is based on fuzzy clustering according to their locations and the sensor nodes belong to a cluster with a specific probability. The energy consumption and the distance factors of a WSN are considered to design the fitness function. These works have shown the advantages of optimisation through PSO. To the best of our knowledge, there are no previous works which have used PSO to optimise node degree, node centrality and packet drop probability to find the cluster heads. Therein lies the novelty of this work.",
